The Rays will send Drew Rasmussen to the mound for Wednesday’s matinee series finale against the Tigers. Rasmussen has been pitching well, 3-1 with a 2.67 ERA and 3-0, 1.25 in his last four starts. The Tigers will start lefty Eduardo Rodriguez, whom the Rays know well from his time with the Red Sox. The teams split the first two games of the series. The Rays are off Thursday and then go to Baltimore for a quick weekend visit. The Rays reinstated reliever Phoenix Sanders (back) from the injured list and optioned the USF product to Durham, where he had been rehabbing. Here is the Rays’ lineup: And for the Tigers: • • • Sign up for the Rays Report weekly newsletter to get fresh perspectives on the Tampa Bay Rays and the rest of the majors from sports columnist John Romano. Never miss out on the latest with the Bucs, Rays, Lightning, Florida college sports and more. Follow our Tampa Bay Times sports team on Twitter and Facebook.